# Return detailed status objects instead of empty arrays on failure

## Context

Functions that scan directories or read config files should return status objects with distinct states

## Pattern

Instead of returning empty array on any failure, return { data: [], status: 'not_found' | 'empty' | 'error', message: string }. This allows callers to distinguish between 'directory missing', 'directory empty', and 'error reading directory'.

## Example

```typescript
function getHooksFromDir(dir) {
  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {
    return { hooks: [], status: 'not_found', message: `Directory does not exist: ${dir}` };
  }
  // ... handle empty and error states too
}
```

## Why

Silent empty returns force users to guess why nothing was found. Detailed status enables clear error messages and recovery guidance.
